{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Truncate Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Truncate Filter</h1>

<p>Shortens a string to a specified length. If the string is longer than the limit, it is cut and a suffix (default <code>...</code>) is appended. The total output length (including the suffix) equals the specified limit.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "string" | truncate: length %}
{% "string" | truncate: length, "suffix" %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "The quick brown fox" | truncate: 10 %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> The qui...</p>
<p>The string is cut to 7 characters and <code>...</code> (3 characters) is appended, giving a total of 10 characters.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "The quick brown fox" | truncate: 12, " (more)" %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> The q (more)</p>
<p>A custom suffix replaces the default <code>...</code>. The total output is still 12 characters: 5 from the original string plus 7 for the suffix.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "Short" | truncate: 20 %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> Short</p>
<p>If the string is already within the limit, it is returned unchanged — no suffix is added.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>The default suffix is <code>...</code> (three dots, 3 characters).</li>
  <li>The specified length is the <strong>total</strong> output length, including the suffix.</li>
  <li>If the length is less than or equal to the suffix length, only the suffix is returned.</li>
  <li>Length is measured in bytes, not Unicode code points.</li>
</ul>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/strip">strip</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/size">size</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
